(60, 768682959463378670, 'Lille vs Auxerre', 'HOME_WIN', 2, 'Lille are 3rd, only 1 point above Lyon, so they must win to protect direct Champions League status. Auxerre are 15th, level with Nice and still exposed to the relegation playoff. Lille have much higher class.', 9, 8, 8, 4, '[\"Lyon vs Lens\",\"Nice vs Metz\"]', '[\"242952754794341925\",\"114395762091501116\"]', '2026-05-17 05:24:36', '2026-05-17 05:24:36', 'GPT_MANUAL', 10),
(61, 875889815034838435, 'Brest vs Angers', 'HOME_WIN', 2, 'Both sides are mostly safe, but Brest are higher and stronger, while Angers still have a small need to avoid any late danger. Motivation is moderate, class leans Brest.', 4, 5, 5, 4, '[\"Nice vs Metz\",\"Nantes vs Toulouse\"]', '[\"114395762091501116\",\"310279999938265427\"]', '2026-05-17 05:24:36', '2026-05-17 05:24:36', 'GPT_MANUAL', 10),
(62, 987941780007054414, 'Lorient vs Le Havre', 'HOME_WIN', 2, 'Lorient are safe mid-table and stronger. Le Havre are only 1 point above Auxerre and Nice, so they have survival motivation, but their weaker attack and lower table position make Lorient the safer pick.', 3, 8, 5, 4, '[\"Nice vs Metz\",\"Lille vs Auxerre\",\"Nantes vs Toulouse\"]', '[\"114395762091501116\",\"768682959463378670\",\"310279999938265427\"]', '2026-05-17 05:24:36', '2026-05-17 05:24:36', 'GPT_MANUAL', 10),
(63, 655873932854937505, 'Arsenal vs Burnley', 'HOME_WIN', 4, 'Arsenal are 1st with 79 points, only 2 points ahead of Manchester City, with both teams having 2 games left and 6 potential points available. That makes this a very high-pressure title-race match: Arsenal cannot safely drop points. Their +42 goal difference and 68 goals scored show elite team quality. Burnley are 19th with 21 points, 15 points behind 18th-placed West Ham and far beyond survival with only 6 points available, so they are effectively already relegated. Their -36 goal difference and 73 goals conceded suggest a weak defensive profile. Arsenal should dominate, and motivation plus quality heavily favour a comfortable home win.', 10, 1, 10, 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-05-18 11:27:49', '2026-05-18 11:27:49', 'GPT_MANUAL', 10),
(64, 826886104499883895, 'AFC Bournemouth vs Manchester City', 'AWAY_WIN', 3, 'Bournemouth are 6th with 55 points, still strongly motivated to protect Europa League position, with Brighton, Brentford and Chelsea close behind. However, Manchester City are 2nd with 77 points and can still overtake Arsenal if they win both remaining games, so their title motivation is extremely high. City also have much stronger class indicators: higher points, better goals scored, and +43 goal difference versus Bournemouth\'s +4. Expect Bournemouth to compete, but City are more likely to win.', 8, 10, 6, 9, NULL, '[\"720209503409981288\"]', '2026-05-19 12:42:35', '2026-05-19 12:42:35', 'GPT_MANUAL', 10),
(65, 720209503409981288, 'Chelsea vs Tottenham Hotspur', 'HOME_WIN', 3, 'Chelsea are 10th with 49 points but have two games left, so they can still reach 55 and pressure Bournemouth, Brighton and Brentford for European qualification. Their motivation is high despite currently being outside Europe. Tottenham are 17th with 38 points, safe from relegation because West Ham can only reach 39, but they have little positive upside from the table. Chelsea have better points, goal difference and attacking output, while Spurs look like a low-motivation lower-table side. Chelsea home win is the most likely result.', 8, 2, 6, 4, NULL, '[\"826886104499883895\"]', '2026-05-19 12:42:35', '2026-05-19 12:42:35', 'GPT_MANUAL', 10);
