(190, 826886104499883895, 'GPT_MANUAL_DAILY_SAFEST', 300737756271875725, 4, 'Manchester City X2 (double chance) away at Bournemouth looks like the safest available option above 1.20. City are still in the title race with 77 points and two games remaining, meaning every match is effectively must-win to pressure Arsenal on 82 points. Bournemouth are motivated for Europa League qualification at 55 points, but City possess vastly superior squad quality, scoring power (75 goals vs 56), and equal +43 goal difference despite facing stronger pressure all season. The market price of 1.22 reflects City being highly unlikely to lose even away from home.', '2026-05-19 12:54:13', '2026-05-19 13:00:39', 0, 9),
(191, 826886104499883895, 'GPT_MANUAL_DAILY_BEST', 894482512603869930, 3, 'Bournemouth vs Manchester City — Both Teams To Score YES at 1.5 is the strongest value bet in the preferred range. Bournemouth are chasing European qualification and cannot simply defend; they average strong attacking production with 56 goals scored. Manchester City need victory for the title chase and average over two goals per game. Bournemouth have conceded 52 goals, while City have scored 75, so City should create many chances. At the same time Bournemouth\'s home motivation and attacking urgency make a home goal very realistic.', '2026-05-19 12:54:13', '2026-05-19 13:00:39', 0, 8),
(192, 720209503409981288, 'GPT_MANUAL_DAILY_UPSET', 762074051441914266, 3, 'Tottenham away win at Chelsea around 3.7 is the most interesting upset angle. Chelsea are more motivated because they still have an outside European push with two matches left, but they remain inconsistent all season at 13 wins, 10 draws and 13 losses. Tottenham are low in the table yet still possess enough attacking quality to hurt Chelsea in an open derby game. London derbies are historically volatile, and Spurs still have enough offensive talent to exploit Chelsea\'s defensive instability despite weaker overall league performance.', '2026-05-19 12:54:13', '2026-05-19 13:00:39', 0, 4),
(193, 826886104499883895, 'GPT_MANUAL_SAFEST_PER_TOURNAMENT', 300737756271875725, 10, 'Manchester City X2 (double chance) away to Bournemouth is the safest qualifying option above 1.20. City are still fully alive in the title race with 77 points and two matches remaining, meaning they effectively must avoid defeat to continue chasing Arsenal on 82 points. Bournemouth are motivated because they sit 6th with Europa League qualification pressure from Brighton, Brentford and Chelsea behind them, but City\'s superior quality is clear: 75 goals scored, only 5 losses all season, and a +43 goal difference. Even with Bournemouth fighting hard at home, City avoiding defeat is highly probable.', '2026-05-19 13:00:26', '2026-05-19 13:00:38', 0, 9),
(194, 826886104499883895, 'GPT_MANUAL_BEST_PER_TOURNAMENT', 894482512603869930, 10, 'Bournemouth vs Manchester City — BTTS YES at 1.5 stands out as the best balance of value and probability. Bournemouth are highly motivated to secure European football and cannot sit back defensively, especially at home. They have scored 56 goals this season and face a City side that will aggressively push for victory because of the title race. Manchester City average elite attacking numbers with 75 goals scored, while Bournemouth have conceded 52. Both teams have strong reasons to attack, making goals at both ends very likely.', '2026-05-19 13:00:26', '2026-05-19 13:00:38', 0, 8),
(195, 720209503409981288, 'GPT_MANUAL_UPSET_PER_TOURNAMENT', 651706047858847571, 5, 'Chelsea vs Tottenham draw at 3.87 is the most attractive upset-style outcome. Chelsea are more motivated due to a possible late push toward European qualification, but they have been inconsistent all season with a perfectly balanced 13-10-13 record. Tottenham sit 17th and have little table pressure, which can sometimes make them dangerous and more open in derby matches. Both teams concede regularly and neither has shown elite control this season. A tense, chaotic London derby ending level is realistic at strong odds.', '2026-05-19 13:00:26', '2026-05-19 13:00:38', 0, 5),
(196, 826886104499883895, 'GET_ONE_BEST_FOR_EVENT_DEFAULT', 204294329626175036, 5, 'Manchester City is highly motivated to win as they are still in contention for the Premier League title. The handicap line of Manchester City -1 offers value at 2.6 odds, as they are in strong form and need a result to pressure Arsenal. With two games remaining and a strong squad, City can cover this handicap against a mid-table Bournemouth, whose motivation for Europa League is less pressing.', '2026-05-19 13:01:03', '2026-05-19 13:03:25', 0, NULL),
(197, 720209503409981288, 'GET_ONE_BEST_FOR_EVENT_DEFAULT', 762074051441914266, 3, 'Tottenham is still fighting for Premier League survival and has motivation, making the away win at 3.7 odds a strong value bet compared to implied probability, given Chelsea\'s mid-table position and lower motivation.', '2026-05-19 13:01:08', '2026-05-19 13:03:25', 0, NULL),
(198, 826886104499883895, 'GET_ONE_SAFEST_FOR_EVENT_DEFAULT', 769462643214566206, 5, 'Manchester City has high motivation to secure full points in the title race, and the \'AWAY\' handicap (-1) at 1.22 provides value with reasonable safety, reflecting City\'s likely push for a decisive win.', '2026-05-19 13:01:19', '2026-05-19 13:03:25', 0, NULL),
(199, 720209503409981288, 'GET_ONE_SAFEST_FOR_EVENT_DEFAULT', 631655239261721702, 15, 'Chelsea has nothing to play for, but Tottenham is close to relegation and very motivated. A \'Draw No Bet\' on Chelsea offers good balance with decent odds for a team not facing strong incentives from Tottenham.', '2026-05-19 13:01:23', '2026-05-19 13:03:23', 0, NULL),
(200, 826886104499883895, 'GET_ONE_UPSET_FOR_EVENT_DEFAULT', 1131652762651938937, 2, 'AFC Bournemouth, in position to secure a Europa League spot with high motivation, face Manchester City, already comfortable in Champions League qualification but distant from the title. The odds on a Bournemouth home win are high at 4.55, suggesting City may not be as focused or intense, making this a plausible upset scenario.', '2026-05-19 13:01:44', '2026-05-19 13:03:23', 0, NULL),
(201, 720209503409981288, 'GET_ONE_UPSET_FOR_EVENT_DEFAULT', 203867391954698923, 5, 'Tottenham is facing relegation threat with remaining games and potential points to stay safe, while Chelsea has no outcome pressure. As these teams meet, Spurs will be highly motivated for a result, making the Draw No Bet for Tottenham at odds of 2.62 a plausible upset with calculated risk.', '2026-05-19 13:01:54', '2026-05-19 13:03:23', 0, NULL);
